-- Italy's Anima says net inflows at 470 mln euros in June
-- By Agnieszka Flak
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 05:05AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, July 9 (Reuters) - Italian asset manager Anima Holding <ANIM.MI> said on Wednesday it had recorded net inflows of around 470 million euros ($641 million) in June, reaching a year to date amount of around 5 billion euros.

Total assets under management stood at 53.46 billion euros at the end of June, up 29 percent from the same period the previous year, Anima said in a statement.